The examples in this directory are not finished.
Sorry.


rrd-client.pl does NOT have any special Perl requirements and does not
need rrdtool or RRD::Simple to be installed.

rrd-server.pl DOES require rrdtool and RRD::Simple to be installed.

rrd-browse.cgi DOES require a number of modules (see list below).


Software required:
==================
perl-5.8.8.tar.gz
rrdtool-1.2.13.tar.gz

Modules required:
=================
libwww-perl-5.805.tar.gz
Compress-Zlib-1.41.tar.gz
Config-General-2.31.tar.gz
HTML-Parser-3.54.tar.gz
HTML-Tagset-3.10.tar.gz
HTML-Template-2.8.tar.gz
HTML-Template-Expr-0.07.tar.gz
Module-Build-0.2801.tar.gz
Parse-RecDescent-1.94.tar.gz
RRD-Simple-1.39.tar.gz
URI-1.35.tar.gz



Notes:
======

# Send from the client to a remote server
*/4 * * * * sleep 20; /usr/bin/perl /home/nicolaw/svn/RRD-Simple/examples/data_gathering/rrd-client.pl 2>/dev/null | /usr/bin/POST http://merry.ntl.tfb.net/rrd-cgi-bin/rrd-server.cgi >/dev/null

# Pipe client to server
*/4 * * * * sleep 20; /home/system/rrd/bin/rrd-client.pl | /home/system/rrd/bin/rrd-server.pl -u merry.tfb.net

# Send over the network using netcat
/home/system/rrd/bin/rrd-client.pl | nc -p 4444 merry.tfb.net
nc -l -p 4444 | /home/system/rrd/bin/rrd-server.pl -u arwen.tfb.net

